exports[`orchestrate — contracts & runbook > golden shape (paths normalized) > RUNBOOK.md 1`] = `
"# ultrasec — sequential RUNBOOK (eco / no-subagent fallback)

Run: \`<RUN>\` · Repo: \`<REPO>\` · Engine: \`node <ENGINE>\`

Generated by \`ultrasec orchestrate\` from the CURRENT run state. This sequential path is
correctness-identical to the multi-agent workflows — same worklists, same contracts, same
conservative folds; only wall-clock differs. Fan-out is an optimization, not a requirement.

## Phase status

| Phase | Worklist | Status | Produce it with |
|---|---|---|---|
| adjudicate | \`<RUN>/findings.json\` | ready (1 item(s)) | \`node <ENGINE> scan --repo <REPO> --out <RUN>\` |
| verify | \`<RUN>/VERIFY.todo.json\` | ready (2 item(s)) | \`node <ENGINE> verify --run <RUN>\` |
| revalidate | \`<RUN>/REVALIDATE.todo.json\` | ready (2 item(s)) | \`node <ENGINE> revalidate --run <RUN>\` |
| investigate | \`<RUN>/INVESTIGATE.todo.json\` | ready (1 item(s)) | \`node <ENGINE> investigate --run <RUN>\` |

## The loop (play every role yourself, one item at a time)

1. **Scan** (if not done): \`node <ENGINE> scan --repo <REPO> --out <RUN>\` → \`<RUN>/findings.json\` (+ optionally prime \`node <ENGINE> context\`).
2. **Investigate the attack surface** (discovery) — \`node <ENGINE> investigate --run <RUN>\` writes \`<RUN>/INVESTIGATE.todo.json\`. For EVERY region, apply \`<RUN>/orchestration/agents/hunter.md\` yourself; merge the grounded Discovery[] into \`<RUN>/orchestration/out/investigate/INVESTIGATE.json\`. Then ingest (citation-checked): \`node <ENGINE> investigate --apply <RUN>/orchestration/out/investigate/INVESTIGATE.json --run <RUN>\`.
3. **Adjudicate the open candidates** — the worklist is \`<RUN>/findings.json\` itself (every \`status: "open"\` candidate). For EVERY open id, apply \`<RUN>/orchestration/agents/analyzer.md\` yourself (\`node <ENGINE> dossier <id> --run <RUN>\`, read every hop, verdict supported/partial/unsupported/refuted + note, exploitPath when supported); merge the verdicts into \`<RUN>/orchestration/out/adjudicate/verdicts.json\`. Then fold, conservatively: \`node <ENGINE> verify --apply <RUN>/orchestration/out/adjudicate/verdicts.json --run <RUN>\`.
4. **Verify adversarially** — \`node <ENGINE> verify --run <RUN>\` writes \`<RUN>/VERIFY.todo.json\` (the still-pending findings). For EVERY entry, apply \`<RUN>/orchestration/agents/skeptic.md\` yourself (try to REFUTE; uncertain high-severity stays needs-human); merge into \`<RUN>/orchestration/out/verify/verdicts.json\`. Then: \`node <ENGINE> verify --apply <RUN>/orchestration/out/verify/verdicts.json --run <RUN>\`.
5. **Revalidate against git history** — \`node <ENGINE> revalidate --run <RUN>\` writes \`<RUN>/REVALIDATE.todo.json\`. For EVERY entry, apply \`<RUN>/orchestration/agents/revalidator.md\` yourself (still-valid/fixed/false-positive/uncertain + note, fixedIn when fixed); merge into \`<RUN>/orchestration/out/revalidate/REVALIDATE.json\`. Then: \`node <ENGINE> revalidate --apply <RUN>/orchestration/out/revalidate/REVALIDATE.json --run <RUN>\`.
6. **Gate**: \`node <ENGINE> check --run <RUN> --semantic\` must exit 0 before presenting anything.
7. **Render**: \`node <ENGINE> render --run <RUN>\` (optionally author the narrative first: \`node <ENGINE> narrative --run <RUN>\`). Loop from step 2 on a new sub-question until a round surfaces nothing new.

With subagents available, prefer the emitted workflows instead: \`orchestrate --run <RUN> --phase <p>\` then \`Workflow({ scriptPath: "<RUN>/orchestration/<p>.workflow.mjs" })\` — you stay the sole writer either way.
"
`;

exports[`orchestrate — contracts & runbook > golden shape (paths normalized) > adjudicate.workflow.mjs 1`] = `
"export const meta = {"name":"ultrasec-adjudicate","description":"Adjudicate the 1 open candidate(s) of an ultrasec audit from dossier evidence (analyzer fan-out, conservative fold)","phases":[{"title":"Adjudicate"}]}

// NOT a plain Node script: launch via the Workflow tool — Workflow({ scriptPath: "<RUN>/orchestration/adjudicate.workflow.mjs" }).
// Emitted by \`ultrasec orchestrate\` from the CURRENT worklist. The worklist is the source
// of truth: if it changes, re-run \`orchestrate --phase adjudicate\` before launching.

// Constants for THIS run (injected at emit time; no Date.now/Math.random in this harness).
const RUN = "<RUN>"
const ENGINE = "<ENGINE>"
const WORKLIST = "<RUN>/findings.json"
const AGENTS = RUN + '/orchestration/agents'
const BATCHES = [["9b0bcc91ea6a"]]
const SCHEMA = {"type":"object","required":["verdicts"],"properties":{"verdicts":{"type":"array","items":{"type":"object","required":["id","verdict","note"],"properties":{"id":{"type":"string"},"verdict":{"enum":["supported","partial","unsupported","refuted"]},"note":{"type":"string","description":"one line grounded in the source you read, citing [file:line]"},"exploitPath":{"type":"string","description":"REQUIRED for supported: who · what they send · what they get"}}}}}}

function contract(name, extra) {
  return 'Read and follow the dispatch contract at ' + AGENTS + '/' + name + '.md VERBATIM.\\n'
    + 'Constants: RUN=' + RUN + '  ENGINE=' + ENGINE + '  WORKLIST=' + WORKLIST + '.\\n'
    + 'Invoke the engine only by its ABSOLUTE path: node ' + ENGINE + ' <cmd> — read-only commands only.'
    + (extra ? '\\n' + extra : '')
}

log('ultrasec adjudicate: ' + "1" + ' item(s) across ' + BATCHES.length + ' agent(s)')

phase("Adjudicate")
const results = await pipeline(BATCHES, (batch, _item, i) =>
  agent(contract('analyzer', 'ITEMS=' + batch.join(',')), { label: 'adjudicate:' + (i + 1), phase: "Adjudicate", agentType: 'general-purpose', schema: SCHEMA }))

// One-writer rule: this workflow only COLLECTS verdicts fragments. The main agent merges
// the returned \`verdicts\` arrays into <RUN>/orchestration/out/adjudicate/verdicts.json, then runs the conservative fold:
//   node <ENGINE> verify --apply <RUN>/orchestration/out/adjudicate/verdicts.json --run <RUN>
return { phase: "adjudicate", worklist: WORKLIST, results: results.filter(Boolean) }
"
`;

exports[`orchestrate — contracts & runbook > golden shape (paths normalized) > skeptic.md 1`] = `
"# Contract: skeptic

You are an adversarial skeptic verifying the pending findings of an ultrasec audit. Assume each claim is wrong until the source proves it — try to REFUTE it.

Worklist: \`<RUN>/VERIFY.todo.json\` (a JSON array; each entry has \`id\`, \`severity\`, \`cwe\`, \`title\`, \`category\`, \`claim\`, \`files[]\`; repo root: \`<REPO>\`). Handle ONLY the entries whose \`id\` is named in your prompt (\`ITEMS=<id,…>\`). If an \`ITEMS\` id is no longer in the worklist, skip it and say so in your note.

For EACH of your entries:

1. Open every cited \`file:line\` in \`files[]\` and read it in context; run \`node <ENGINE> dossier <id> --run <RUN>\` (read-only) for the full cross-file packet.
2. Judge the claim against the source — is the flow **real and exploitable**?
   - \`supported\` — real and exploitable exactly as claimed (include \`exploitPath\`).
   - \`partial\` — a real issue, but the claim overstates it (wrong hop, narrower reach, weaker impact).
   - \`unsupported\` — the source does not establish the claim.
   - \`refuted\` — the source contradicts the claim (name the guard/sanitizer \`[file:line]\`).
3. Be skeptical, but do NOT dismiss a high/critical finding unless you can positively **refute** it — the fold sends an \`unsupported\`/\`partial\` high-severity finding to **needs-human**, never auto-dropped. Uncertain ⇒ leave it for a human.
4. \`note\` is REQUIRED — one line grounded in what you read, citing resolvable \`[file:line]\`. If the entry carries a \`priorSignal\`, it is a HINT, never a verdict — adjudicate yourself.

Return (structured output): \`{ "verdicts": [{ "id", "verdict", "note", "exploitPath" }] }\` — your ITEMS only.

## Return, don't write

Return ONLY the structured output specified above. Do NOT write, edit, or delete any file; do NOT run any engine command that writes (\`scan\`, \`import\`, any stage's emit or \`--apply\` — \`verify\`, \`triage\`, \`revalidate\`, \`investigate\`, \`context\`, \`narrative\`, \`implement\`, \`render\`, \`clean\`, \`run\`). The only engine commands you may run are the read-only ones: \`dossier\`, \`graph\`, \`paths\`, \`tools\`. The orchestrator is the sole writer — it merges your fragments into one apply file itself and runs the conservative \`--apply\` fold. Exception: if a justification is prose too large to return, write ONLY to \`<RUN>/orchestration/out/<role>-<batch>.md\` (a file namespaced to you alone) and return its path.
"
`;
